##Glory! When the first heroes of the Shanghai Hubei Medical Team returned to Shanghai, Li Qiang went to the airport to greet them

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

Li Qiang, the party secretary of Shanghai, greeted the soldiers at the airport, welcoming them safely and successfully on behalf of the municipal government and the people of the city.

Sorting out | Shen Lin

March 18, the first batch of back to Shanghai Hubei Medical team home.

In the afternoon, a total of 47 Shanghai medical team members, including 12 from Huashan Hospital and 35 from Dongfang Hospital, returned to Shanghai on the chartered flight of China Eastern Airlines MU9003 from Wuhan. Around 6 pm, the medical team members arrived at Hongqiao Airport. Li Qiang, secretary of Shanghai Municipal Party Committee, greeted them at the airport.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image source | Hubei Medical Team

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Earlier, just this morning, the convoy of the national emergency medical rescue team from Mount Hua Hospital first arrived in Shanghai and was greeted by a line of police officers as it passed through the toll gate at Huaqiao, Jiading District.

Video | Xinmin Evening News

It is reported that in order to ensure the safe return of all personnel, the rescue team has developed a strict standard disinfection process, completed the final disinfection in Wuhan: The use of 1000 MG / L of effective chlorine to kill items, vehicles and air are killed by 500 dioxidochlorine(.) Aerosol sprays.

On the way back to Shanghai, the traffic police of Hubei lined up to salute and greet the Shanghai medical team

Upon return to Shanghai, all personnel were quarantined for 14 days at designated isolation points and placed under medical observation; vehicles were also sealed for two weeks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medical staff's Special Air ticket photo source | Hubei Medical Team

That night, Wuhan authorities released 32 Thanksgiving posters, which wrote the words of gratitude to the Shanghai Medical Team: Although thousands of miles apart, a river to the heart.

Image Source | Wuhan Culture and Tourism Bureau

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The national medical team went home in groups

From January 24 to March 8,42,600 people from 346 medical teams traveled to Wuhan and Hubei after the outbreak of NCP. Among them, Shanghai 9 medical teams altogether 1649 medical personnel ride to Wuhan, and the National Medical Team in the same boat, day and night fighting.

On March 16, the Central Working Leading Group on the response to the epidemic of new coronavirus held a meeting. The meeting made it clear that the formulation of an orderly plan to organize the evacuation of medical personnel in Hubei by batches.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Comrades-in-arms from Hubei and Shanghai bid farewell to each other

Yesterday afternoon (March 17) , the Wuhan East West Lake Shelter Hospital, where the status of Wuhan Living Room Exhibition Hall was restored, members of the Hubei medical team from all over again reunited. Politburo member of the Communist Party of China Sun Chunlan, Vice Premier of the State Council and head of the central guidance team, saw off some of the national emergency medical rescue teams that were leaving soon. Chen Yixin, deputy head of the central guidance team and secretary general of the Central Political and Legal Affairs Commission, ying Yong, the party secretary of Hubei Province, was also there.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Sun Chunlan said that the medical teams should ensure the treatment needs of local patients on the basis of orderly, safe and smooth withdrawal, there is still a medical team to withdraw, to assume the emergency and critical care tasks of the final withdrawal.

It is worth mentioning that after the farewell ceremony, Ying Yong, the party secretary of Hubei Province, walked up to the members of the Shanghai medical team and said with a smile: "before I saw you off in Shanghai, now I will see you off in Hubei. Drive slowly and pay attention to your safety! "

We will not rest until we have won the war

On February 4, Huashan Hospital in Wuhan supported the Wuhan National Emergency Medical Rescue Team, the third group of Mount Hua Hospital supported the Wuhan Medical Team, which was the first medical team to be stationed in the Wuchang Shelter Hospital, the first patients were admitted on February 5th. (related: How does a Shelter Hospital respond to "receiving and receiving" ? A question from Ma Xin, commander of the Hubei Medical Team of the Mount Hua Hospital.)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the afternoon of March 10, the last batch of 49 patients was discharged from the Wuchang Shelter Hospital of Hongshan Stadium in Wuhan and declared to be closed. Over the course of 35 days, Wuchang's shelter hospital has evolved into a series of "firsts" : the first to be put into use, the first to set up a temporary party committee, the first to discharge patients, the first to start patient counselling, and the last to have a rest cabin.

After the closure of the Wuchang Shelter Hospital, the rescue team of the Mount Hua Hospital also carried out various kinds of data collation, reviewed the medical history of the discharged patients, and further improved the diagnosis and treatment routine of the Shelter Hospital, the hospital flu flow and other systems, hope to be able to provide very valuable practical experience for the later National Disaster Relief and epidemic prevention and control.

After receiving the evacuation order on March 15, the rescue team of Mount Hua Hospital drew up the evacuation plan, made clear the evacuation personnel, and completed all kinds of preparations for the evacuation of the mobile hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yesterday's farewell ceremony, Mount Hua Hospital Vice President Maxin as Mount Hua Hospital shelter medical team leader, also came to the scene to attend the farewell meeting. "Today we are mainly here to see off our comrades, who still need to hold out a little longer, " said Feng Shengjie of Mount Hua Hospital.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ma Xin, deputy director of Mount Hua Hospital, as the leader of the Mount Hua Hospital's shelter medical team, came to the scene to participate in the farewell ceremony

It turned out that in addition to some of the team members returning to Shanghai first, another 26 members of the team took the initiative to stay in the Intensive Care Unit of the Tongji Hospital affiliated to the Tongji Medical College and continue to participate in the prevention and control of the epidemic, we were determined to win the battle of Hubei and win the battle of Battle of Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image source | Hubei Medical Team

The experience of Shanghai in the Shelter Hospital

Speaking of this more than a month of anti-epidemic experience, the East Hospital Deputy Director Lei Han heart mixed feelings. At first, the doctors in the Shelter Hospital were too busy. To this end, Lei Han figured out the assistant doctor system, that is, to select those senior, experienced, smart nurses, follow the doctor rounds, write down and help implement the doctor's orders; Visit the patients, after finding problems with the doctor feedback, and start to solve; help doctors and patients to communicate and explain, effectively solve the problem of inadequate doctors. Related Reading: What does Wuhan's intensive construction of a "shelter hospital" reveal

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dong Fang Hospital Vice President, East West Lake Shelter Hospital Shanghai Aid Hubei Medical Team Leader Lei Han picture source | view news

Later, he also proposed the responsibility area of the doctors on duty in the shelter and the system of the person in charge of the patients, which effectively solved the management problems brought by the huge number of patients. According to incomplete statistics, the rescue team's doctors entered the cabin on duty 99 times, each time 6 hours. Managed 120 patients in hall a and 413 patients in Hall B. Including admission of new patients, 285 patients, 157 patients discharged from hospital. The "three zero" goals of zero recall of patients, zero infection of medical staff and zero death of patients have been successfully achieved.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image Credit: Onscreen News

March 7 afternoon, Wuhan east-west Lake Shelter Hospital rest cabin, medical team into the cabin finishing, washing, drying machinery and equipment, such as medical robots. Up to the eve before returning to Shanghai, the members of the medical team were still tidying up their tents until late at night.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the evening of March 16, the medical team of the Eastern Hospital in Hubei Province received instructions to return to the shelter and start packing tents

"everyone was a little bit excited when they heard the news of their return. The separation from their families for nearly two months was a deep desire to be reunited, but there was still a sense of frustration and sadness at the thought that many classmates and fellow soldiers were still holding on. We hope that we can play to our strengths and ensure the health of the people of Shanghai after our return,"said Hua Jing of Dongfang Hospital.

In addition, Sun Guixin, the executive leader of the International Emergency Medical Team of the Oriental Hospital, told the media that the medical team has recently joined forces with hospitals in Wuhan and medical teams from various provinces, regions and cities to assist Wuhan in fighting the epidemic, plan to formulate "Chinese standard for Shelter Hospital" (temporary name) . He said: "I hope that the national efforts to combat the new outbreak of pneumonia experience practices put into words, for the world to learn from. "
